How you make an impact:
You will be responsible for deep diving into our customer data to identify and optimise opportunities to increase our revenue and our customers' engagement. You will be instrumental in accelerating sales growth and increasing customer retainment by conducting ongoing strategic analysis by interpreting large volumes of data from multiple sources to identify campaign targets.

You add value by:
Conducting analysis to determine market segments, developing strategy, visualising and executing on insights and post implementation performance;
Analysing our customer data and build campaigns that improve customer understanding and drive engagement;
Devising and implementing customer behavioural analysis and provide actionable insights
Conducting customer analytics to form the basis for continuous optimisation of value propositions;
Contributing to initiatives designed to understand key behaviours that drive customer acquisition, engagement and retainment; and
Analysing the results of campaigns and strategic activities, presenting key findings and guiding sales, marketing and other stakeholders on particular course of action that provides an optimal business outcome


About you:
We're looking for someone who has strong analytical and problem-solving skills, a high level of accuracy and attention to detail , with excellent organisational and time management skills with an ability to consistently work to meet deadlines. You should have excellent written and verbal communication skills and the ability to present complex information simply and directly to all levels of the business. It is also essential that you have the ability to accurately extract, manipulate and interpret multiple large datasets.

Your Experience:
At least 3yrs experience extracting key insights from large volumes of data to drive customer journey strategy
Experience with campaign targeting and management
Advanced Excel and the ability to build complex reports
Advanced MS Office / G-Suite
Experience with BI Tool (Tableau CRM, Google BI, Tableau, Cognos) desirable


