Ramsay Health Care is investing to build our global strategic sourcing capabilities. With an ambitious growth agenda, we are seeking an experienced Procurement Analyst to help drive value across the company for internal stakeholders.
The Role
Reporting to the Group Procurement Manager, you will support the Procurement Managers to:
Build strategic sourcing capabilities
Help shape category strategies through analysis, evaluation and research
You will also be responsible for:
Completing market research, identifying external trends, capturing industry benchmarks, analysing data and spend, building business models;
Building a solid fact base of spend data by category;
Helping shape category strategies;
Highlighting and reducing supply risk;
Assisting in the negotiation of supplier agreements to ensure they deliver best price, quality and service to Ramsay;
Identifying and evaluating cost saving opportunities;
Automating routine reporting and performance trackers;
Building relevant business scorecards and performance trackers;
Reporting on key performance measures and indicators to help drive value across the company;
Monitoring and tracking savings to ensure targets are met;
Supporting key procurement processes, systems and tools; and
Supporting all team members.
About You:
To be successful in this role, you will have the following criteria:
Essential:
Minimum 3 years’ experience in a data analyst role in finance, procurement, or supply chain;
Tertiary qualification in a discipline such as Business, Accounting, Finance, Contract Law, Logistics, Supply Chain Management, Industrial Engineering;
Strong knowledge of SAP;
Highly developed analytical, evaluation and research skills including demonstrated ability to implement new concepts and deliver positive, innovative solutions and savings;
Strong commercial acumen;
Ability to gather, interpret and report on data;
Demonstrated capability in Microsoft office and other business intelligence software; and
Knowledge of the organisation: Our Values, Code of Conduct and The Ramsay Way.
Desirable:
Experience within the private health sector;
Procurement experience;
Project management experience;
Proven ability to manage and implement change successfully; and/or
International exposure
The Company:
Ramsay Health Care was established in 1964 and has grown to become a global hospital group operating 480 facilities across 11 countries, making it one of the largest and most diverse private healthcare companies in the world, and the largest in Australia. Ramsay Health Care is well-respected throughout the health care industry for operating quality private hospitals and for its excellent record in hospital management and patient care. Its focus is on maintaining the highest standards of quality and safety; being an employer of choice and operating its business according to The Ramsay Way philosophy: “People Caring for People”.
