About the Business
Braithwaite Steiner & Pretty Pty Ltd trading as Odgers Berndtson discovers and nurtures the best executive talent in the market.
Our mission is to establish Odgers Berndtson among the top global search firms. This will enable us to work on the most important assignments, to attract and retain the best talent into our business and to deliver work that our clients can be proud of. This requires us to deliver market-leading quality, to look and be consistent and to bring the most appropriate expertise to bear on our work by collaborating. Our core values are teamwork, expertise, integrity, and rigour. Our underlying ethos is that what we do matters because our work affects lives and helps transform organisations – so we have a responsibility to do it excellently.
We have an opportunity for an experienced Business & Systems Analyst to join our Information Technology team, located in Sydney.
Primarily the role of the Business & Systems Analyst is the continual review, improvement and management of the Company’s existing and future Financial Business & Systems processes ensuring optimal business performance. The work will require partnering closely with both the Management and the Finance teams to formulate strategy and execute roadmap transforming existing financial reporting into data-driven Dashboards (Microsoft Power BI) featuring intuitive KPIs and CSFs.
You will be expected to progress very quickly and become a subject-matter expert in our business systems.
Key criteria and role responsibilities
· Developing new applications, procedures, reports and scripts, and maintaining/developing Interfaces between the Finance System (SunSystems) and other internal/external Systems such as Selenity Expenses, ETZ Timesheets, Salesforce, and the in-house Management Information System;
· Analysing and investigating existing processes, identifying, and assessing inefficiencies, and providing recommendation on improvements to procedures, automation opportunities, systems functionality, and behaviours;
· Working with internal/external stakeholders to elicit and document requirements for new Systems Applications/Components;
· Applying established data and process modelling techniques to illustrate, model and specify operations for use in design and development phases;
· Creation and execution of test plans to confirm system integrity and requirements have been delivered upon;
· Writing System instruction manuals and facilitating workshops to train end users on new or improved systems / processes;
· Assessment of potential emerging/new Systems and subsequent project management of implementation;
· Extracting raw data from multiple sources, resolving errors and redundancy, and converting it into structured data for manipulation and visualization in Microsoft Power BI;
· Troubleshooting Systems and Data issues ensuring timely resolution;
· Working closely with the Finance Team, producing monthly information for management, ensuring integrity of data and reports; creating new financial models in Excel and automating processes using VBA;
· Acting as an agent of change and project lead for Finance Systems projects applying appropriate methodologies to develop plans, ensure cross-functional collaboration, and delivery. Providing counsel to decision making stakeholders.
Skills & Experience
Formal undergraduate associate degree or degree qualification;
Minimum 10 years relevant and related professional work experience. Post graduate qualifications are highly regarded;
Demonstrated experience working in an application support or development background and recent systems analysis experience;
Experience in dealing effectively with multiple user demands;
Writing and executing SQL scripts and macros.
Other position requirements
Demonstrated ability to establish and maintain positive working relationships;
Outstanding verbal and written communication skills marked by adaptability, precision, and nuance;
Collaborative with strong interpersonal skills and team focused and the ability to engage and influence others through effective verbal and written communication skills with the ability to communicate information clearly and accurately and resolve issues with stakeholders at all levels;
The proven ability to manage multiple projects and to prioritise, monitor and co-ordinate personal workload, with minimal supervision to achieve agreed outcomes within specified timeframes;
Recognise opportunities to enhance service delivery and capitalise on these through contributing to the development of improved processes, projects, and practices;
Sharp and rigorous analytical skills and attention to detail with a can-do attitude and a passion to solve problems with a commitment to delivering successful results individually or through a team.
Applying
· Applications are to include a cover letter (1-2 pages) outlining what excites you about the role and our business, and why your skills and experience are what we need. This will be provided together with a current CV which includes a small number of highly relevant Referees.
· Applications to be submitted in MS Word format
· Only applicants who address and meet the selection criteria will be considered and only successful candidates will be contacted for an interview.
